# Datasole Project Rules

## Quality Gate

Two gate levels: `npm run gate` (local, fast, no bench) and `npm run gate:full` (CI, includes perf benchmarks).

**Run `npm run gate` after making changes.** It is enforced by:
- pre-commit hook: lint-staged (format + lint staged .ts files)
- pre-push hook: `npm run gate` (no bench — fast for iteration)
- CI: `npm run gate:full` + demo install/build. Auto-commits artifacts with `[skip ci]`
- Nightly: upgrades all deps, runs `gate:full`, commits with `[skip ci]`

`npm run dist` is an alias for `npm run gate`.

## Commit Messages

Lead with **intention** (the _why_), not a list of what changed. Use Conventional Commits types (`feat`, `fix`, `refactor`, `chore`, `docs`, `test`, `perf`, `ci`, `build`). Include `[ADR-XXX]` when applicable. Bot/CI commits use `[skip ci]` to prevent re-triggering.

## Documentation

Canonical documentation lives in `docs/`. Consult before making structural changes:
- `docs/tutorials.md` — Progressive learning examples (update when adding user-facing features)
- `docs/examples.md` — Copy-paste recipes by pattern
- `docs/architecture.md` — System design, wire protocol
- `docs/decisions.md` — Architecture Decision Records
- `docs/contributing.md` — Build commands, workflow

## Architecture Decisions

All ADRs in `docs/decisions.md`. When changing deps, protocol, build, transport, state sync, adapters, public API, or the quality gate pipeline: check existing ADRs, add new ones if needed, reference in commit messages.

## Code Organization

- `src/shared/` — Zero-dep code shared between client/server (includes CRDTs)
- `src/client/` — Browser library (no Node.js APIs)
- `src/server/` — Node.js library (may use Node builtins)
- Dependency direction: shared ← client, shared ← server. No client↔server imports.

## Build Constants

`src/shared/build-constants.ts` is the single source of truth for version, protocol version, and defaults. Never hardcode these values elsewhere.

## Changelog

Update `CHANGELOG.md` (Keep a Changelog format) when bumping `package.json` version. Group under Added/Changed/Deprecated/Removed/Fixed/Security. Use SemVer: major = breaking, minor = features, patch = fixes.

## Type Safety

- No `any` in public API surfaces
- Generic type parameters on RPC, events, and state APIs
- All exports ship `.d.ts` declarations
